g.text: The share of cancer deaths from each cancer, between 2018-2022 in the United States, using ICD-10 113 category codes
Which cancers are people dying from at different ages?
Data source: CDC Wonder database, using data on the underlying cause of death from 2018–2022
For clarity, several cancer categories have been merged. 'Lymphatic and blood cancers' includes Hodgkin disease, Non-Hodgkin lymphoma, multiple myeloma, and other lymphoid and blood cancers.
'Head, neck, and oral cancers' includes oral, pharyngeal, and laryngeal cancers. 'Other/unspecified cancers' combines in situ, uncertain, benign, and other unspecified cancers.
